  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 16:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ὑποκριταὶ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",[710] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "hypocrites",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The hypocrisy was their greater skill in natural than in spiritual things; for they who have the former have much less excuse than dull men for being wanting in the latter, although they are often wanting in it. For an example of both united, see ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 2:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρόσωπον τοῦ οὐρανοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the countenance of the sky",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "face",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". A man’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "countenance",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " varies, his ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "face",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is always the same. An instance of Prosopopœia,[711] as just before in the word ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΣΤΥΓΝΆΖΩΝ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "lowering",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τὰ σημεῖα τῶν καιρῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the signs of the times) i, e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", those which are suitable to (congruentia) each time. Our Lord indicates, that not only are times to be distinguished by their signs, but also signs by the character of the times, and signs and the kinds of them from each other. For the mode of God’s dealing with man[712] is various—by various doctrines, persons, signs, times—all of which correspond among themselves: wherefore different signs suit different times. Those signs, less splendid indeed, but such as were altogether beneficial to man on earth (see ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 9:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), were suitable to the Messiah then being on earth; see ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 9:54",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Wherefore it was incumbent upon them to obtain proofs, not from heaven, but from themselves: see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 12:57",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". For the same reason, after His ascension our Lord did not exhibit signs on earth, as He had previously done.[713]—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Οὐ ΔΎΝΑΣΘΕ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "are ye not able?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") sc. to distinguish sign from sign:—said with astonishment. If you wished it, you could do so most fully: as it is, you are prevented from doing so by a voluntary blindness.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
